27#include <sys/cdefs.h>
28__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_bus_nv50.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
29
30#include "priv.h"
31
32#include <subdev/therm.h>
33#include <subdev/timer.h>
34
35static int
36nv50_bus_hwsq_exec(struct nvkm_bus *bus, u32 *data, u32 size)
37{
38 struct nvkm_device *device = bus->subdev.device;
39 int i;
40
41 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001098, 0x00000008, 0x00000000);
42 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001304, 0x00000000);
43 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
44 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001400 + (i * 4), data[i]);
45 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001098, 0x00000018, 0x00000018);
46 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00130c, 0x00000003);
47
48 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
49 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001308) & 0x00000100))
50 break;
51 ) < 0)
52 return -ETIMEDOUT;
53
54 return 0;
55}
56
57void
58nv50_bus_intr(struct nvkm_bus *bus)
59{
60 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &bus->subdev;
61 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
62 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001100) & nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001140);
63
64 if (stat & 0x00000008) {
65 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x009084);
66 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x009088);
67
68 nvkm_error(subdev, "MMIO %s of %08x FAULT at %06x\n",
69 (addr & 0x00000002) ? "write" : "read", data,
70 (addr & 0x00fffffc));
71
72 stat &= ~0x00000008;
73 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001100, 0x00000008);
74 }
75
76 if (stat & 0x00010000) {
77 struct nvkm_therm *therm = device->therm;
78 if (therm)
79 nvkm_subdev_intr(&therm->subdev);
80 stat &= ~0x00010000;
81 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001100, 0x00010000);
82 }
83
84 if (stat) {
85 nvkm_error(subdev, "intr %08x\n", stat);
86 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001140, stat, 0);
87 }
88}
89
90void
91nv50_bus_init(struct nvkm_bus *bus)
92{
93 struct nvkm_device *device = bus->subdev.device;
94 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001100, 0xffffffff);
95 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001140, 0x00010008);
96}
97
98static const struct nvkm_bus_func
99nv50_bus = {
100 .init = nv50_bus_init,
101 .intr = nv50_bus_intr,
102 .hwsq_exec = nv50_bus_hwsq_exec,
103 .hwsq_size = 64,
104};
105
106int
107nv50_bus_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_bus **pbus)
108{
109 return nvkm_bus_new_(&nv50_bus, device, index, pbus);
110}
